# Alembic migrations for jerryib_trade

Quick start:

1) Set DATABASE_URL
   export DATABASE_URL='postgresql+psycopg://user:pass@localhost:5432/jerryib_trade'

2) Upgrade to latest
    poetry run alembic upgrade head

3) Verify with psql

    Note: psql does NOT understand the SQLAlchemy '+psycopg' suffix.
    You can quickly transform the URL:

       export PSQL_URL="${DATABASE_URL/+psycopg/}"
       psql "$PSQL_URL" -c '\\dt'

Common commands:

- Show current revision:
   poetry run alembic current

- Show history:
   poetry run alembic history --verbose

- Create a new revision (autogenerate from ORM metadata):
   poetry run alembic revision -m "your message" --autogenerate

- Downgrade one step (use with care):
   poetry run alembic downgrade -1

Notes:

- The application can still run without DB enabled.
- For existing databases created via Base.metadata.create_all(), run the bootstrap migration to add missing columns/constraints.

Tips:

- Alembic will use DATABASE_URL if set; otherwise it falls back to alembic.ini.
